  "text": "Balb/c bone marrow cells were differentiated into bone marrow-derived DCs (BMDCs) by 6-day culture in the presence of granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF, 25 ng/mL; R&D Systems, Minneapolis, MN) with or without VAF347 (20 nM). On day 6, some of the cells were activated with LPS (1 g/mL; Sigma-Aldrich) for 8 hours. BMDCs were injected intravenously (3 ϫ 10 5 ) into diabetic Balb/c female 1 day prior to islet allograft transplantation. To evaluate their stimulatory capacity, irradiated BMDCs were used as stimulators for responder C57Bl/6 splenocytes (SPCs) (R/S ϭ 10:1). [CITATION_1] H-thymidine was added after 96 hours of culture for an additional 18 hours.",
